Farmers harvest cabbage in a greenhouse in Beizhuangzi Village, Zhangjiakou, North China's Hebei Province on Wednesday. The village, located in a frigid zone, used to be poverty-stricken. It has taken advantage of local climate conditions to plant vegetables that can endure frigid weather, as part of targeted poverty alleviation efforts. Photo: VCGÂ  
